<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-160-162  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 160 162.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Business  April 3 1989 v15 n7 p139(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Electronics companies' profits rise 3.2% in 1988. (BusinessBarometer)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Baatz, Elizabeth.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Profits for the electronics industry fell 9.9 percent in the 4thqtr 1988.andP;  Profits rose 41 percent in 1987 and only 3.2 percent in1988.andP;  Growth in revenue held steady at 12.3 percent.andP;  The majorreason for the sluggish profit growth was the rising prices ofmemory chips.andP;  It is also speculated that production slowed downbecause supplies were scarce in 1988, and that this may result inincreased production in 1989.andP;  The fall of the dollar made USproducts more competitive internationally and export profitsincreased as a result.andP;  Continued growth in revenue is forecast.andO;Input costs are expected to fall, exports to decrease and profitsto remain steady.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Electronic IndustrySemiconductor industryComputer industrySalesStatisticsExportProfitRevenueForecasting.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Electronic business indexes: revenue and profit. (graph)Revenue growth for electronics companies. (graph)Leading indicators; Semiconductor sales and book-to-bill ratio.andO;(graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>